---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="Curriculum Vitae" currentPath="/cv/">
  <div class="pb-32 px-6 md:px-12 max-w-[1440px] mx-auto w-full">
    <!-- Hero Section / Title -->
    <section class="grid grid-cols-12 gap-8 mb-24 min-h-[30vh] items-end">
      <div class="col-span-12 flex flex-col justify-end">
        <h1
          class="text-[4rem] md:text-[8rem] font-black leading-[0.9] tracking-tighter uppercase mb-4"
        >
          Software<br />Engineer
        </h1>
        <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row gap-8 md:gap-24 mt-8 lg:mt-12">
          <p
            class="text-[0.75rem] md:text-sm uppercase tracking-[0.2em] font-bold text-primary"
          >
            Software Design Architect
          </p>
          <p
            class="text-[0.75rem] md:text-sm uppercase tracking-[0.2em] font-bold text-on-surface/50"
          >
            Eindhoven, Netherlands
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <div class="h-px w-full bg-on-surface/10 mb-24"></div>

    <!-- Experience Section -->
    <section class="grid grid-cols-12 gap-8 mb-32">
      <div class="col-span-12 md:col-span-4 mb-8 md:mb-0">
        <h2 class="text-[2rem] font-black tracking-tighter uppercase mb-8">
          Experience
        </h2>
        <p
          class="text-[0.75rem] uppercase tracking-[0.1em] text-on-surface/40 leading-relaxed max-w-[250px]"
        >
          Specializing in safety-critical systems, avionics and embedded
          software architectures. <br /><br /> Actively learning and applying <strong
            >Artificial Intelligence</strong
          > across personal and professional projects.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="col-span-12 md:col-span-8 flex flex-col gap-16">
        <!-- Job 1 -->
        <div class="flex flex-col gap-4">
          <div
            class="flex justify-between items-baseline border-b border-on-surface/5 pb-4"
          >
            <h3 class="text-[1.5rem] font-bold tracking-tight">
              Software Engineer / ASML
            </h3>
            <span class="text-[1rem] font-black tabular-nums"
              >07.2022 — PRESENT</span
            >
          </div>
          <p class="text-on-surface/70 leading-relaxed max-w-2xl text-sm">
            Spearheaded software development and engineering within the MX
            Exposure Imaging division, focusing on <strong
              >DUV (Deep Ultraviolet) Image Align Software</strong
            >. Architected and implemented robust solutions utilizing <strong
              >C</strong
            >, <strong>Python</strong>, and <strong>Julia</strong>.
            Additionally, served as <strong>Scrum Master</strong>, facilitating <strong
              >agile methodologies</strong
            > and optimizing team delivery pipelines.
          </p>
          <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 mt-2">
            <span
              class="text-[0.65rem] border border-on-surface/10 px-2 py-1 uppercase tracking-wider font-bold"
              >C</span
            >
            <span
              class="text-[0.65rem] border border-on-surface/10 px-2 py-1 uppercase tracking-wider font-bold"
              >Python</span
            >
            <span
              class="text-[0.65rem] border border-on-surface/10 px-2 py-1 uppercase tracking-wider font-bold"
              >Julia</span
            >
            <span
              class="text-[0.65rem] border border-on-surface/10 px-2 py-1 uppercase tracking-wider font-bold"
              >Scrum</span
            >
            <span
              class="text-[0.65rem] border border-on-surface/10 px-2 py-1 uppercase tracking-wider font-bold"
              >DUV Exposure</span
            >
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Job 2 -->
        <div class="flex flex-col gap-4">
          <div
            class="flex justify-between items-baseline border-b border-on-surface/5 pb-4"
          >
            <h3 class="text-[1.5rem] font-bold tracking-tight">
              MIDAS Team Lead & Architect / ICterra
            </h3>
            <span class="text-[1rem] font-black tabular-nums"
              >11.2021 — 06.2022</span
            >
          </div>
          <p class="text-on-surface/70 leading-relaxed max-w-2xl text-sm">
            Led a cross-functional team in the research and development of <strong
              >MIDAS</strong
            >, an early diagnosis and tracking system for breast cancer,
            developed in collaboration with Hacettepe University Hospital.
            Engineered a <strong>multi-stage neural network classifier</strong> to
            detect malignant sections in mammogram images, effectively handling <strong
              >multi-view</strong
            >, <strong>multi-class</strong>, and <strong
              >imbalanced datasets</strong
            >. Designed and deployed a <strong
              >containerized, remote-execution architecture</strong
            > maximizing <strong>multi-GPU Unix workstations</strong> for intensive
            model training. Also managed the maintenance of mission-critical firmware
            for the <strong>Mobile Digital XRAY System (MXRAY)</strong> project on
            behalf of Aselsan.
          </p>
          <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 mt-2">
            <span
              class="text-[0.65rem] border border-on-surface/10 px-2 py-1 uppercase tracking-wider font-bold"
              >Python</span
            >
            <span
              class="text-[0.65rem] border border-on-surface/10 px-2 py-1 uppercase tracking-wider font-bold"
              >Deep Learning</span
            >
            <span
              class="text-[0.65rem] border border-on-surface/10 px-2 py-1 uppercase tracking-wider font-bold"
              >Neural Networks</span
            >
            <span
              class="text-[0.65rem] border border-on-surface/10 px-2 py-1 uppercase tracking-wider font-bold"
              >TensorFlow</span
            >
            <span
              class="text-[0.65rem] border border-on-surface/10 px-2 py-1 uppercase tracking-wider font-bold"
              >Keras</span
            >
            <span
              class="text-[0.65rem] border border-on-surface/10 px-2 py-1 uppercase tracking-wider font-bold"
              >Docker</span
            >
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Job 3 -->
        <div class="flex flex-col gap-4">
          <div
            class="flex justify-between items-baseline border-b border-on-surface/5 pb-4"
          >
            <h3 class="text-[1.5rem] font-bold tracking-tight">
              IMODE Team Lead & Senior SDE / Turkish Aerospace
            </h3>
            <span class="text-[1rem] font-black tabular-nums"
              >03.2019 — 11.2021</span
            >
          </div>
          <p class="text-on-surface/70 leading-relaxed max-w-2xl text-sm">
            Directed the <strong>IMODE</strong> (Integrated Model-Based Design Environment)
            product lifecycle, a proprietary <strong
              >model-based design suite</strong
            > competing with <strong>VAPS</strong> and <strong>SCADE</strong>.
            Managed the development of critical modules including the <strong
              >ARINC 661 Toolkit</strong
            >, <strong>AADL Architecture Design Toolkit</strong>, and <strong
              >DO-178C Tool Qualification Kits</strong
            >. Engineered core system components using <strong>C++</strong> and <strong
              >Qt Framework</strong
            >, developing a multilingual <strong>code generator</strong> and orchestrating
            <strong>GUI model designs</strong> for the Advanced Jet Trainer. Served
            as <strong>Scrum Master</strong> and Co-instructor for the Model-Based
            Design course at Yildiz Technical University.
          </p>
          <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 mt-2">
            <span
              class="text-[0.65rem] border border-on-surface/10 px-2 py-1 uppercase tracking-wider font-bold"
              >C++</span
            >
            <span
              class="text-[0.65rem] border border-on-surface/10 px-2 py-1 uppercase tracking-wider font-bold"
              >Qt Framework</span
            >
            <span
              class="text-[0.65rem] border border-on-surface/10 px-2 py-1 uppercase tracking-wider font-bold"
              >System Architecture</span
            >
            <span
              class="text-[0.65rem] border border-on-surface/10 px-2 py-1 uppercase tracking-wider font-bold"
              >DO-330</span
            >
            <span
              class="text-[0.65rem] border border-on-surface/10 px-2 py-1 uppercase tracking-wider font-bold"
              >Code Generation</span
            >
            <span
              class="text-[0.65rem] border border-on-surface/10 px-2 py-1 uppercase tracking-wider font-bold"
              >ARINC 661</span
            >
            <span
              class="text-[0.65rem] border border-on-surface/10 px-2 py-1 uppercase tracking-wider font-bold"
              >Agile</span
            >
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Job 4 -->
        <div class="flex flex-col gap-4">
          <div
            class="flex justify-between items-baseline border-b border-on-surface/5 pb-4"
          >
            <h3 class="text-[1.5rem] font-bold tracking-tight">
              Software Design Engineer / Aselsan (via Turkish Aerospace)
            </h3>
            <span class="text-[1rem] font-black tabular-nums"
              >08.2017 — 03.2019</span
            >
          </div>
          <p class="text-on-surface/70 leading-relaxed max-w-2xl text-sm">
            Developed <strong>Operational Flight Program (OFP)</strong> software for
            the New Generation Trainer Aircraft. Produced <strong
              >safety-critical system requirements</strong
            > and <strong>C++</strong> source code utilizing <strong
              >IBM Rational Rhapsody</strong
            >. Key engineering contributions included the design and
            implementation of the <strong
              >Identification Friend or Foe (IFF) Transponder</strong
            >, <strong>Cockpit Voice Recorder (CVR)</strong>, and <strong
              >Flight Data Recorder (FDR)</strong
            > modules. Orchestrated the initial development of advanced radar display
            pages utilizing <strong>VAPS</strong> and actively participated in rigorous
            <strong>software verification</strong> processes.
          </p>
          <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 mt-2">
            <span
              class="text-[0.65rem] border border-on-surface/10 px-2 py-1 uppercase tracking-wider font-bold"
              >C++</span
            >
            <span
              class="text-[0.65rem] border border-on-surface/10 px-2 py-1 uppercase tracking-wider font-bold"
              >Embedded Software</span
            >
            <span
              class="text-[0.65rem] border border-on-surface/10 px-2 py-1 uppercase tracking-wider font-bold"
              >Avionics</span
            >
            <span
              class="text-[0.65rem] border border-on-surface/10 px-2 py-1 uppercase tracking-wider font-bold"
              >RTOS</span
            >
            <span
              class="text-[0.65rem] border border-on-surface/10 px-2 py-1 uppercase tracking-wider font-bold"
              >IBM Rational Rhapsody</span
            >
            <span
              class="text-[0.65rem] border border-on-surface/10 px-2 py-1 uppercase tracking-wider font-bold"
              >DO-178C</span
            >
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Job 5 -->
        <div class="flex flex-col gap-4">
          <div
            class="flex justify-between items-baseline border-b border-on-surface/5 pb-4"
          >
            <h3 class="text-[1.5rem] font-bold tracking-tight">
              Software Design Engineer / Turkish Aerospace
            </h3>
            <span class="text-[1rem] font-black tabular-nums"
              >08.2016 — 08.2017</span
            >
          </div>
          <p class="text-on-surface/70 leading-relaxed max-w-2xl text-sm">
            Built low-level <strong>Line Replaceable Unit (LRU) firmware</strong
