              >C</span
            >
            <span
              class="text-[0.65rem] border border-on-surface/10 px-2 py-1 uppercase tracking-wider font-bold"
              >C#</span
            >
            <span
              class="text-[0.65rem] border border-on-surface/10 px-2 py-1 uppercase tracking-wider font-bold"
              >.NET Framework</span
            >
            <span
              class="text-[0.65rem] border border-on-surface/10 px-2 py-1 uppercase tracking-wider font-bold"
              >Bootloader</span
            >
            <span
              class="text-[0.65rem] border border-on-surface/10 px-2 py-1 uppercase tracking-wider font-bold"
              >I2C</span
            >
            <span
              class="text-[0.65rem] border border-on-surface/10 px-2 py-1 uppercase tracking-wider font-bold"
              >ARINC 429</span
            >
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Job 6 -->
        <div class="flex flex-col gap-4">
          <div
            class="flex justify-between items-baseline border-b border-on-surface/5 pb-4"
          >
            <h3 class="text-[1.5rem] font-bold tracking-tight">
              Software Engineer / AYESAŞ
            </h3>
            <span class="text-[1rem] font-black tabular-nums"
              >08.2014 — 08.2016</span
            >
          </div>
          <p class="text-on-surface/70 leading-relaxed max-w-2xl text-sm">
            Established firmware requirements via <strong
              >IBM Rational DOORS</strong
            > for critical <strong>Line Replaceable Units (LRUs)</strong> on the New
            Generation Trainer Aircraft. Separately, for a MALE-class Unmanned Aerial
            Vehicle project, authored primary lifecycle documentation and implemented
            <strong>C/Assembly</strong> source code for <strong
              >Board Support Packages (BSPs)</strong
            > and <strong>IO Drivers</strong>. This included the primary <strong
              >Bootloader</strong
            > for configuring the <strong>Minimum Processing Environment</strong
            >, <strong>Dataloader</strong> modules, and robust <strong
              >device drivers</strong
            > for <strong>Ethernet, Serial, Flash, and NVRAM</strong> hardware.
          </p>
          <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 mt-2">
            <span
              class="text-[0.65rem] border border-on-surface/10 px-2 py-1 uppercase tracking-wider font-bold"
              >C</span
            >
            <span
              class="text-[0.65rem] border border-on-surface/10 px-2 py-1 uppercase tracking-wider font-bold"
              >Assembly</span
            >
            <span
              class="text-[0.65rem] border border-on-surface/10 px-2 py-1 uppercase tracking-wider font-bold"
              >Embedded Software</span
            >
            <span
              class="text-[0.65rem] border border-on-surface/10 px-2 py-1 uppercase tracking-wider font-bold"
              >BSP & IO Drivers</span
            >
            <span
              class="text-[0.65rem] border border-on-surface/10 px-2 py-1 uppercase tracking-wider font-bold"
              >DO-178C</span
            >
            <span
              class="text-[0.65rem] border border-on-surface/10 px-2 py-1 uppercase tracking-wider font-bold"
              >DOORS</span
            >
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Job 7 -->
        <div class="flex flex-col gap-4">
          <div
            class="flex justify-between items-baseline border-b border-on-surface/5 pb-4"
          >
            <h3 class="text-[1.5rem] font-bold tracking-tight">
              Software Engineer / Bilişim AŞ
            </h3>
            <span class="text-[1rem] font-black tabular-nums"
              >06.2013 — 08.2014</span
            >
          </div>
          <p class="text-on-surface/70 leading-relaxed max-w-2xl text-sm">
            Contributed to the development, maintenance, and technical support
            of the Directorate General of Civil Aviation (DGCA) Information
            Administration System using <strong>JavaServer Faces (JSF)</strong>.
            Additionally, engaged in an R&D initiative to build a comprehensive <strong
              >Business Intelligence Application</strong
            > utilizing a diversified technology stack including <strong
              >PHP, Java, and JavaScript</strong
            > across multiple database management systems.
          </p>
          <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 mt-2">
            <span
              class="text-[0.65rem] border border-on-surface/10 px-2 py-1 uppercase tracking-wider font-bold"
              >Java</span
            >
            <span
              class="text-[0.65rem] border border-on-surface/10 px-2 py-1 uppercase tracking-wider font-bold"
