    </section>

    <div class="h-px w-full bg-on-surface/10 mb-24"></div>

    <!-- Education Section -->
    <section class="grid grid-cols-12 gap-8 mb-32">
      <div class="col-span-12 md:col-span-4 mb-8 md:mb-0">
        <h2 class="text-[2rem] font-black tracking-tighter uppercase mb-8">
          Education
        </h2>
      </div>

      <div class="col-span-12 md:col-span-8 flex flex-col gap-12">
        <div
          class="flex flex-col md:flex-row justify-between gap-4 border-b border-on-surface/5 pb-6"
        >
          <div>
            <h3 class="text-[1.25rem] font-bold">
              MSc. in Multimedia Computing
            </h3>
            <p class="text-on-surface/60 text-sm mt-1">
              Middle East Technical University / Machine Learning, Signal
              Processing
            </p>
            <p class="text-on-surface/40 text-[0.75rem] italic mt-2">
              Thesis: Speaker and Posture Classification using Instantaneous
              Acoustic Features of Breath Signals
            </p>
            <div class="mt-6">
              <img
                id="thesis-figure"
                src="/images/thesis-infographic.png"
                alt="Master's Thesis Infographic: The Science of Breath"
                class="w-full max-w-2xl rounded-sm border border-on-surface/10 shadow-sm cursor-zoom-in hover:opacity-90 transition-opacity"
              />
            </div>
            <p
              class="text-on-surface/70 leading-relaxed text-sm mt-4 max-w-2xl"
            >
              Developed a novel <span class="font-bold"
                >hybrid CNN-RNN architecture</span
              > to classify speakers and physical postures using acoustic breath signals.
              I curated <span class="font-bold">BreathBase</span>, a
              comprehensive dataset of over 5,000 instances, to train and
              evaluate deep learning models. By employing the <span
                class="font-bold">Hilbert-Huang Transform</span
              >, I extracted high-dimensional features from non-stationary
              signals. Through optimization with <span class="font-bold"
                >LSTM/GRU layers</span
              > and <span class="font-bold">model ensembling</span>, the system
              achieved <span class="font-bold">87% speaker identification</span> and
              <span class="font-bold">98% posture recognition</span> accuracy, significantly
              outperforming traditional <span class="font-bold">SVM</span> and <span
                class="font-bold">kNN-DTW</span
              > baselines.
            </p>
          </div>
          <span class="text-[1rem] font-black tabular-nums md:text-right"
            >2016 — 2019</span
          >
        </div>
        <div
          class="flex flex-col md:flex-row justify-between gap-4 border-b border-on-surface/5 pb-6"
